        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks FMM for his "Lectures [on Mr Darwin’s philosophy of language", <hi rend="italic">Fraser’s Mag.</hi> n.s. 7 (1873): 525–41, 659–78].</p>  
<p>CD is not worthy to be FMM’s adversary as he knows very little about language and, being fully convinced man is descended from some lower animal, he is forced to believe <hi rend="italic">a priori</hi> that language has developed from inarticulate cries.</p> 
        </abstract>
